    "body": "## Motivation\n\nWhen compiling DeepGeMM for Kimi K2 EP+DP+TP 32, I hit a DeepEP timeout:\n\n```\nFile \"/root/code/.venv/lib/python3.12/site-packages/sglang/srt/layers/moe/token_dispatcher/deepep.py\", line 458, in _dispatch_core\n    ) = buffer.dispatch(\n        ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n  File \"/root/code/.venv/lib/python3.12/site-packages/deep_ep/buffer.py\", line 376, in dispatch\n    return self.internode_dispatch(x, handle, num_tokens_per_rank, num_tokens_per_rdma_rank, is_token_in_rank,\n           ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\n  File \"/root/code/.venv/lib/python3.12/site-packages/deep_ep/buffer.py\", line 489, in internode_dispatch\n    recv_src_meta, send_rdma_head, send_nvl_head, event = self.runtime.internode_dispatch(\n                                                          ^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^^\nRuntimeError: DeepEP error: timeout (dispatch CPU)\n```\n\nCompile only happens on `local_rank=0` on each node, however, each node can compile at a different speed. Say DeepEP timeout is 100s — if the compile time differs by more than 100s across nodes, we hit the DeepEP timeout. This symptom is amplified when chunked prefill size is large (I set it to `8192*32`, so per-DP chunk prefill size is 8192).\n\n## Modifications\n\n1. **Add torch distributed barrier before EP all-to-all (`deepep.py`)**: DeepEP's all-to-all has a much shorter timeout compared to `torch.distributed`. By adding a barrier before each EP all-to-all during the compile stage, DeepEP is protected by the much longer torch distributed timeout. The barrier is only active during the compile stage to avoid extra overhead at runtime.\n\n2. **Send warmup requests to all DP ranks (`compile_deep_gemm.py`)**: Previously, the custom warmup stage (`warm_up_compile`) only sent a request to one rank. In the EP+DP+TP 32 case, only the first node was compiled, but the rest were not. In the actual warmup stage, requests go to each DP rank, but only the first node has cache — resulting in very different forward times that can hit the timeout even with the torch distributed barrier. The fix sends warmup requests to all DP ranks so every node compiles during the custom warmup stage.\n\nCo-authored-by: Cheng Wan <ch-wan@users.noreply.github.com>",
